<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0c8caceb-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s80t–4"><num value="80t–4">§ 80t–4.</num><heading> Educational and liaison programs</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0c8cacec-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s80t–4/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Programs authorized</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Museum may carry out educational and liaison programs in support of the goals of the Museum.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0c8caced-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s80t–4/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Collaboration with schools</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out this section, the Director shall carry out educational programs in collaboration with elementary schools, secondary schools, and postsecondary schools.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0c8cacee-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/260/dT/tI/s106">Pub. L. 116–260, div. T, title I, § 106</ref>, <date date="2020-12-27">Dec. 27, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/2276">134 Stat. 2276</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
